# AGENTS.md maintenance

`services/<name>/AGENTS.md` is the **source of truth** for that service (API, env, workers, adapters, data model).
Root [AGENTS.md](../AGENTS.md) indexes services; [docs/onboarding/README.md](../docs/onboarding/README.md) describes cross-service flows.

## When to update (same change set as code)

Update the relevant docs when you change:

- HTTP/gRPC routes or auth model
- Env vars, ports, DB name
- Background workers (poll interval, claimed events)
- Outbox event names, producers, consumers
- Billing entitlements or consume/release semantics
- Adapter dependencies (service A → service B)
- Directory layout or CQRS usecase packages

## Which files

| Change scope | Update |
|--------------|--------|
| Single service | `services/<name>/AGENTS.md` + `services/<name>/.cursor/rules/service.mdc` if it duplicates facts |
| Cross-service flow | above + `docs/onboarding/README.md` |
| Future scale design | `docs/architecture/outbox-relay.md` (relay only; not implemented) |

## Rules

- Do **not** document aspirational behavior — only what the code does today.
- If code and doc disagree, **fix the doc** or **fix the code** in the same PR; never leave drift.
